Thorax.
pronotum (
Fig. 13–16
) semicircular, 1,5x longer than head length, approximately 1,3x wider than long, lightly punctated with shallows and equidistant punctures in the anterior most area, except for a marginal single line of deeper and distinct punctures, with short and upright bristles, lateral margins almost subparallel, slightly divergent posteriad and slightly declined in lateral view, disc slightly convex, posterior margin almost as wide as distance between elytral humeri, anterior angle rounded. Hypomeron (
Fig. 15
